HEADWORD: Norfolk spaniel
<hw>Norfolk spaniel</hw>. <def>One of a breed of field spaniels similar
to the clumbers, but shorter in body and of a liver-and-white or
black-and-white color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

